However, the contents of these constituents differed according to the plant part and gender.
This was the ﬁrst report of antifungal activity of curzerene, explaining partially the activity

Bioautography assay helped to detect antifungal fractions in a complex matrix of essential oils and
guided to the isolation of target-directed constituents. Further studies are necessary to isolate higher
amounts of pure curzerene, in order to test its limit of detection.
